[~alice], [~ccassler]: I ssh'd into the clchost for shared setup #1 (10.111.1.71) and checked the code in /usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/eucaconsole/static/js/pages/elb_view.js .  Looks as though the old code (w/o the fix) is still there...

{code}
    475             if (!$scope.vpcNetwork) {  // Bypass rules check on non-VPC clouds
    476                 $scope.elbForm.submit();
    477             }
{code}

See https://github.com/eucalyptus/eucaconsole/pull/1641 for what line 475 should be.  Same problem for elb_wizard.js, line 712.  Could you confirm if shared setup 1 has the latest eucaconsole package?

/cc [~tony]

[~kgill], shared 1 is now updated and I verified the fix is there. Well I may have to do more work b/c the console on that setup is behind a load balance and I only updated the packages that were on the CLC. Shared #2 is good to go.

{code}
    475             if ($scope.vpcNetwork === 'None') {  // Bypass rules check on non-VPC clouds
    476                 $scope.elbForm.submit();
    477             }
{code}
